cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ACRF: Agent Communication Risk Framework"
message: "If you use ACRF in your work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Sekar
    given-names: Kanna
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0003-7470-1432"
  - family-names: Sankara Narayanan
    given-names: Ravi Karthick
repository-code: "https://github.com/kannasekar-alt/acrf"
url: "https://github.com/kannasekar-alt/acrf"
abstract: >-
  ACRF is a cross-framework risk methodology for securing agent-to-agent
  (A2A) communications. It defines 10 critical risk dimensions  - each
  cross-mapped to the OWASP Agentic Top 10 and OWASP MCP Top 10  - with
  AIVSS severity scoring and concrete defense patterns. First presented
  at RSA Conference 2026.
keywords:
  - ai-security
  - agent-security
  - multi-agent-systems
  - agent-to-agent
  - a2a
  - llm-security
  - ai-risk
  - threat-modeling
  - owasp
  - mcp-security
